
## 1. Rate Limiting (Infrastructure Protection)
- [*] Connect [limmiter.py](file:///c:/Users/sp710/Desktop/ResumeAnalizer/backend/Middleware/limmiter.py) safely to [redis_cache.py](file:///c:/Users/sp710/Desktop/ResumeAnalizer/backend/Middleware/redis_cache.py).
- [*] Define global limit of ~100 requests / minute for non-auth routes.
- [*] Define strict limit of ~5 requests / minute for `/auth/login` and `/auth/signup`.
- [*] Define hyper-strict limit for `/resumes/upload` to prevent OpenAI spam.

## 2. API Caching (Read-Heavy Endpoints)
- [ ] Implement short-lived caching for the `/user/` (Profile) endpoint.
  - TTL: 5 minutes.
  - Invalidate cache automatically if the user updates their profile.
- [ ] Implement short-lived caching for `/user/resumes` (Dashboard list).
  - TTL: 60 seconds (prevents reload spam against Postgres + MinIO).

## 3. Background Processing (FastAPI + Celery + Redis)
- [ ] Set up Celery to use Redis as the Message Broker (`broker_url`).
- [ ] Setup Celery to use Redis as the Result Backend (`result_backend`).
- [ ] Refactor the Resume Upload endpoint to hand off processing to a Celery `@task`.
- [ ] Update POST `/resumes/upload` to immediately return `{"status": "Processing"}` cleanly without waiting for AI.

## 4. AI & Vector Optimization (The Money Saver)
- [ ] Build a hashing utility for incoming AI text queries (e.g., `md5(job_description)`).
- [ ] Before calling OpenAI's `ada-002` embedding API, check Redis for `embedding:{hash}`.
- [ ] If found: Immediately pass the cached vector to Qdrant.
- [ ] If missing: Call OpenAI, then store the result `redis.setex(f"embedding:{hash}", 86400, vector_data)`.
